Class CvtrResult

java.lang.Object
CvtrResult
public class CvtrResult
extends java.lang.Object
The Convertator Result maintains information about equation result fields so that the base and units may be changed easily.

    • CvtrResult

      public CvtrResult​(boolean base, java.lang.String abbrev, double conversion, int typeIndex, int unitIndex)
      The Convertator Result constructor sets the class fields from the supplied parameters.
      Parameters:
      base - If true, the result base, otherwise a unit in the result.
      abbrev - The unit or base abbreviation.
      conversion - The conversion value of a unit.
      typeIndex - The index of the result's Type.
      unitIndex - The unit's index in the Unit array.

  • Method Details

    • setBase

      public void setBase​(int baseIndex, java.lang.String baseAbbrev)
      Set a new base to be used to display the equation result.
      Parameters:
      baseIndex - The value of the new base index from the CvtrEngine.
      baseAbbrev - The abbreviation of the new base from the CvtrEngine.

    • setUnit

      Parameters:
      unitIndex - The value of the new unit index.
      unitAbbrev - The abbreviation of the new unit.
      unitConversion - The conversion factor for the new unit.
